title: God's Own Country
subTitle: The lives of a taxi driver, a man travelling to Kerala and a public prosecutor intertwine with each other as they seek monetary aid and justice.

title: Pathemari
subTitle: Narayanan, a young man, goes to Dubai to make a living. However, he faces many struggles but braves them for the sake of his family's well-being.

title: Jawan of Vellimala
subTitle: The villagers of Vellimala force the government to build a dam in their village. However, when the dam becomes unsafe, the government decides to destroy it, leading to violent protests by the villagers.

title: Chirikkum Thalika
subTitle: A comprehensive compilation of some of the best rib-tickling comedy scenes from various Malayalam movies featuring renowned actors and actresses.

title: Kadha, Samvidhanam Kunchakko
subTitle: Kunchacko, a millionaire who built his fortune through questionable means, marries Mary and vows to change. However, leaving his past behind proves to be harder than he imagined.

title: Happy Husbands
subTitle: The lives of three happily married men are turned upside down by the arrival of a bar singer. They are later reunited during a holiday in Malaysia.

title: Bangalore Days
subTitle: Three cousins, Divya, Krishnan and Arjuna, share a close bond and decide to move to Bangalore to fulfil their childhood dreams. There, they face challenges that will change their lives forever.

title: Pulimurugan
subTitle: A small village seeks help from a man with extraordinary force to protect them against man-eating tigers and the drug mafia.

title: Vellinakshathram
subTitle: Aswathy, who to a royal family with dark secrets, falls in love with Vinod. However, strange events being occuring after Aswathy mysteriously dies during childbirth.

title: Drishyam 2
subTitle: Georgekutty, a cinema hall owner, is a changed man who thrives in life. However, when his family become entangled in a criminal investigation, he must protect them from the legal institution.

title: June
subTitle: June, a teenager, believes that there is nothing remarkable about her. She experiences adolescent crushes, handles heartbreaks and fights insecurities as she grows into a mature and confident woman.

title: June

title: Rosapoo
subTitle: Shajahan struggles to make ends meet after suffering a huge loss in his duty-free shop. His friend Neeraj, who aspires to become a director, ropes Shajahan into his idea of making an adult film.

title: Sullu
subTitle: Jithu, a carefree boy, gets trapped in an abandoned house, forcing him to reflect on his life and appreciate what he once took for granted.

title: Bhaagamathie
subTitle: Chanchala, an IAS officer, is imprisoned in a haunted house for interrogation. However, things take an unexpected turn when she gets possessed by a spirit.

title: Rappakal
subTitle: Saraswathiyamma is the head of a noble family that treats her servant Krishnan as one of her own sons. When her relatives conspire to sell her house, she and Krishnan set out to save it.

title: Premam
subTitle: Vikram falls in love with different women at various stages of his life and with each experience, he bears the pain and emotions of separation.

title: Jaya Jaya Jaya Jaya Hey
subTitle: Jayabharathi, an ambitious girl, strives to complete her education. However, when her parents marry her off, she attempts to carve an identity for herself.

title: Oru Yamandan Premakadha
subTitle: Lallu, a happy-go-lucky person who loves to hang out with his friends, is in pursuit of true love. One day, he finds a photo of a missing woman, Diya, in the newspaper and feels a spark.

title: Guruvayur Ambalanadayil
subTitle: A young man eagerly awaits his wedding, but fate twists cruelly, forcing him into a lifelong bond with a woman who harbours nothing but resentment for him.

title: Sunday Holiday
subTitle: Unni, who wishes to become a scriptwriter, learns that a director is hospitalised in his locality. He meets him to narrate his story about Amal, a heartbroken man who plans to start life afresh.

title: Kancheepurathe Kalyanam
subTitle: Kalarikkal Achuthankutty and Pattarumatathil Najeeb are best friends and run an event management company. But soon they part ways because Najeeb secretly marries Achuthankutty's sister Athira.

title: Immininalloral
subTitle: Jeevan is a huge fan of Sneha, a popular actress and when she arrives in his village for a movie shoot, the former is under the illusion that they are already married and kidnaps her.

title: Shakespeare M.A. Malayalam
subTitle: Pavithran, a dramatist, goes to a village for inspiration for writing a play. When he comes across Alli, a young woman who is deep in debt, he decides to learn her story for his play.

title: Pullippulikalum Aattinkuttiyum
subTitle: Gopan, a tourist guide, issues a statement against his rival, Kuriyachan, regarding a human trafficking case. However, Kuriyachan seeks revenge against Gopan.

title: Thuruppugulan
subTitle: Menon buys land for his five-star hotel and asks his trusted employee, Sreedharan Unnithan, to take its charge. Years later, Unnithan gets Menon imprisoned in a fake case and Kunjumon helps him.

title: Christian Brothers
subTitle: When the daughter of a minister gets kidnapped, Christy is called upon to rescue her. Although he manages to save her, he himself gets embroiled in the kidnapper's murder.

title: Neymar
subTitle: Kunjava and his mate welcome a tail-wagging friend called Neymar, only to find their lives thrown into complete disarray.

title: Drishyam
subTitle: When his daughter accidentally kills a man in self-defence, Georgekutty uses his film knowledge to cover it up. Even when the investigation catches up with them, Georgekutty looks out for his family.

title: Thanneermathan Dinangal
subTitle: Jaison, a teenager, has a crush on Keerthy, but she does not reciprocate his feelings. To make things worse, he gets in trouble with Ravi, the new teacher who is liked by everyone, especially Keerthy.
